## 1. Primary & Secondary Colors

Define these as CSS variables (or Tailwind overrides) to ensure consistency. All hex codes match Slack’s light-theme values.

```css
:root {
  /* Primary (Brand) */
  --color-primary-purple:   #4A154B; /* Slack Purple (header, primary buttons) */
  --color-primary-blue:     #1264A3; /* Accent Blue (hover states, selected items) */

  /* Secondary (Accents) */
  --color-accent-green:     #2EB67D; /* Online status, success badges */
  --color-accent-yellow:    #ECB22E; /* Away status, warning badges */
  --color-accent-red:       #E01E5A; /* DND status, error badges */

  /* Neutrals (Backgrounds, Text, Borders) */
  --color-bg-white:         #FFFFFF;
  --color-surface-light:    #F8F8F8;
  --color-surface-hover:    #F4F4F4;
  --color-divider:          #E0E0E0;
  --color-disabled:         #C4C4C4;
  --color-text-primary:     #1D1C1D;
  --color-text-secondary:   #616061;
  --color-text-tertiary:    #A3A2A3;
  --color-sidebar-bg:       #F4F5F6;
  --color-channel-bg:       #FFFFFF;
}

/* (Optional) Dark-mode equivalents */
[data-theme="dark"] {
  --color-bg-white:         #1A1D21;
  --color-surface-light:    #2B2D30;
  --color-surface-hover:    #2C2F33;
  --color-divider:          #3A3C3F;
  --color-disabled:         #4A4C50;
  --color-text-primary:     #E1E2E3;
  --color-text-secondary:   #B4B4B5;
  --color-text-tertiary:    #87888A;
  --color-sidebar-bg:       #2B2D30;
  --color-channel-bg:       #2C2F33;
}
Primary Purple (#4A154B): Top header bar, selected sidebar items, primary buttons.

Primary Blue (#1264A3): Hover/active states, focus outlines, links.

Accents (Green/Yellow/Red): Presence indicators, success/warning/error badges.

Neutrals: Backgrounds, text, borders, and hover states.

