4. Spacing System
Slack’s layout follows an 8 px/16 px rhythm. Base unit: 4 px. Use multiples for consistency.

XS (4 px / 0.25 rem)

S (8 px / 0.5 rem)

M (16 px / 1 rem)

L (24 px / 1.5 rem)

XL (32 px / 2 rem)

2XL (48 px / 3 rem)

4.1. Component Spacing Examples
Component	Padding	Margin
Sidebar (vertical)	16 px (1 rem) top/bottom	—
Sidebar item	8 px (0.5 rem) top/bottom	4 px (0.25 rem) between items
Channel pane padding	16 px (1 rem) all around	—
Message list padding	16 px (1 rem) left/right, 16 px top	12 px (0.75 rem) bottom between msgs
Avatar → Text gap	8 px (0.5 rem)	—
Composer container	12 px (0.75 rem) top/bottom, 24 px (1.5 rem) horizontal	—
