CSS Variables vs. Tailwind: You can define all colors, font families, and spacing in your tailwind.config.js as custom tokens, or keep them as CSS variables if not using Tailwind.

Component Library: Build reusable React components (e.g., SidebarItem, MessageBubble, ThreadContainer, PrimaryButton) that reference these variables/utilities to guarantee consistency.

Accessibility: Regularly run contrast checks (e.g., --text-primary on --bg-white) to ensure WCAG AA compliance.

Dark Mode (Future): All :root variables have dark-mode equivalents under [data-theme="dark"]. You can toggle by setting data-theme="dark" on <html> or <body>.


